{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"69655fac-72b9-4329-80f5-53a9f88b3771","content":"Here's the full scan:\n\n## Time-Related Static Dependencies Found: **7 total**\n\n| File | Count | Lines |\n|------|-------|-------|\n| `Services/OrderProcessor.cs` | 4 | 21, 22, 25, 34 |\n| `Services/NotificationService.cs` | 3 | 7, 16, 18 |\n\n**Breakdown:**\n- `DateTime.UtcNow` — 6 occurrences (order creation, expiry calc, logging)\n- `DateTime.Now` — 1 occurrence (receipt string, line 25)\n\n---\n\n## Recommendation: Inject a `TimeProvider`\n\n.NET 8+ ships `System.TimeProvider` (abstract class). For older targets, define your own:\n\n```csharp\n// Abstraction\npublic interface ITimeProvider\n{\n    DateTime UtcNow { get; }\n}\n\n// Production implementation\npublic class SystemTimeProvider : ITimeProvider\n{\n    public DateTime UtcNow => DateTime.UtcNow;\n}\n\n// Test fake\npublic class FakeTimeProvider : ITimeProvider\n{\n    public DateTime UtcNow { get; set; } = new(2026, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0, DateTimeKind.Utc);\n}\n```\n\nThen inject `ITimeProvider` into `OrderProcessor` and `NotificationService` via constructor, replacing every `DateTime.UtcNow` / `DateTime.Now` call with `_timeProvider.UtcNow`.\n\n**Benefits:**\n- Tests become deterministic — you control time exactly\n- No more flaky expiry/date-window tests\n- Single seam to mock for all time-dependent logic\n\nWould you like me to implement this refactoring across both files?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a7a0a18b-c6ab-487c-b420-85a3c7caf9df","outputTokens":427,"requestId":"BD1A:1BD126:1C5F391:201A238:6A07C5B0"},"id":"248ca442-7da3-4824-a146-6d262e9f7fa0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:17:45.644Z","parentId":"611bac03-8de7-44bf-bd27-44badaa9bd63"}
